Bradley Manewill, a learner from the Eljada-Kairos School in Oudtshoorn, was recently included in the Western Cape cricket team for the intellectually impaired.The team will participate in the SA Summer Games for the intellectually impaired that will be hosted in Mpumalanga in October.In 2019 Manewill received the award as the Intellectually Impaired Player of the Season at the Cricket South Africa Annual Awards function.